Converting the dataframe into matrix for SOM model

nt1.train <- as.matrix(scale(nt1))

Creating the Grid for analysis

nt1.grid <- somgrid(xdim = 10, ydim = 10, topo = "hexagonal")

Training the model with new tool 1 data

nt1.model <- som(nt1.train, nt1.grid, rlen = 500, radius = 2.5, keep.data = TRUE,
dist.fcts = "euclidean")

Available outputs from Training SOM model

names(nt1.model)
##  [1] "data"             "unit.classif"     "distances"        "grid"            
##  [5] "codes"            "changes"          "alpha"            "radius"          
##  [9] "user.weights"     "distance.weights" "whatmap"          "maxNA.fraction"  
## [13] "dist.fcts"

Visualizing the Mapping in SOM

plot(nt1.model, type = "mapping", pchs = 19, shape = "round")

Visualization of codes in SOM

plot(nt1.model, type = "codes", main = "Codes Plot", palette.name = rainbow)

Visualization of changes from SOM

plot(nt1.model, type = "changes")

Finding the Quantization Error obtained from trained SOM model

mean(nt1.model$distances)
## [1] 0.6829354
eqmat <- nt1.model$distances
head(eqmat)
## [1] 0.4254252 0.3454840 0.4106810 0.6769998 0.6407686 0.3828648

Visualization of Quantization Error

par(mfrow = c(1,1))
plot(eqmat,xlab = 'samples', ylab = 'value')

Distribution of Quantization Error through a histogram

hist(eqmat)

Finding the threshold value

th <- quantile(eqmat, prob = 0.999)
th
##    99.9% 
## 3.623325

Plotting the Quantization error as function of time and Adding the threshold line to Quantization Error vs Timestamp plot

plot(x=c(1:nrow(nt1)),y= as.vector(eqmat),xlab = 'samples', ylab = 'value',type = 'l')
abline(h = quantile(eqmat, prob = 0.999), col = 'red')
